<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/uwarninwraithlore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Warnin Wraithlore</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/canadak/sig.JPG BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 492<br> <font color=#8B4513>(5/10/01 4:35:18 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/canadak/warnin1.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Still hunting for:</span><hr size=1> I'm not sure if you realize that the gems for the armor can only be bought in stores, and they are quite hefty in price (for boots, arms, guantlets, and helm the gems cost around 600pp).  What I would do while you are receiving help gathering the items is hit a zone that is mroe loot-heavy.  I am not sure of your level as I have fallen out of touch recently due to my temporary abscence from the game, but if you are in the late teen range I would hang in Highpass Hold and collect the bronze weapons and hides and ring armor.  Sarnaks in LOIO aren't so bad for loot but not great.  Once you hit 28 or so there is giant hunting in Frontier and Rathe mountians, that is very good loot.  <br>
<br>
Another thing you can do, but this has to be timed right, is hang out in East and West Commons.  When an orc camp is free waltz in and start whacking em dead (the west commons camp being hte better one, it is near the Kith Forest zone edge).  Collect the belts.  Those babies will sell for around 4-5pp each in prime time in East Commons (I sold 2 8-slot bags for 75pp in like 4 mins one day when saving for my bronze armour).  People with lots of cash buy them for their twinks.  And don't feel bad for taking that much, they are blowing like 5-10k on their little twinks weapon and armor wise so they can afford it.  The reason I say your timing has to be right is that you have to make sure no one is there.  If someone shows up that needs experience and wants to fight there you should either ask if you can stay taking the odd one and offering assistance if they need it, or leave if they really wish you too.  When I was in my younger days, I can't tell you the frustration of going to an orc camp and some level 25+ goon tells you to screw off cause he is farmin da belts.  Or even worse yet, some level 25+ goon crashes the camp and starts stealin the kills.<br>
<br>
I know there is an unwritten rule that if you are at a camp you own it, but when you aren't getting exp then you shouldn't be owning any camp.  And that is unwritten, if a petition goes out you will be removed for your level and even if you were gaining xp you are told flat out to share it.<br>
<br>
Anyway, sorry for the speel.  I know no one in this guild would go about doin that sort of stuff, I just wanted it said.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It is a good general rule for all of us to keep in mind.<br>
<br>
Well, enough ramblin from me.  I hope I helped some.<br>
<br>
